text.tspan: input 16x16 pattern with 6 materials:
After get_edges we have a vector of shared
edges. Each edge is set by two integer lo-
cal coordinates and two materials it con-
tacts to. Below picture shows pair of edges
for each shared edge with a ghost each shif-
ted towards corresponding material. If no
material is set then ghost edge is skipped.
After get_nodes a 16x16 mapping is created
to provide relationship between edges. Node
points to 4 possible adjacent edges. Since
edge knows it's integer coordinates it is
easy to get to node from edge and then to
next edge in loop.
The routine get_faces takes first edge
that still have any material and starts
to advance a loop using shared nodes map-
ping. The direction is chosen to have cur-
rent material on right hand side.
NOTE: edges are modified on that stage:
materials are removed during travel over a
loop (see left bottom red face):
In quad node a 90 turn is forced. After
all faces are done edges has no adjacent
materials anymore:
For each face makeHoles is called. This
routune eats faces from periferial pixels
up to holes and then makes loops the same
way as it was done to create faces.
